         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Facility management services</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="79993000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>CFH Facilities wishes to procure facility management services for the Quadram Institute, a new facility under construction on the Norwich Research Park that will carry out research into food and health sciences, including the diagnosis of gastrointestinal diseases, and clinical trials.</P>
               <P>The new facility represents a capital investment of £ 82 200 000.00 by the Institute of Food Research (IFR), Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital (NNUH), the University of East Anglia (UEA) and Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council (BBSRC). The building will be completed in March 2018.</P>
               <P>CFH Facilities will operate the building on behalf of the Quadram Institute tenants and wishes to implement a Total Facilities Management (TFM) solution where all FM services are provided by a single supplier.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">6278651.00</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="79993100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKH1"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Quadram Institute, Norwich Research Park.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The new building, which is currently under construction, has 13200m2 of laboratory, clinical and office space across four floors. When completed, it will have the capacity for 400 staff with a further 200 patients, trials volunteers and visitors is approx. The activities to be undertaken are summarised below. These are described in detail in the Operational Services Specification document. The contract will run for 5 years.</P>
                  <P>- Management of the Operational Services, Health &amp; Safety, and Helpdesk.</P>
                  <P>- Security and car park management;</P>
                  <P>- Building, installations and asset maintenance;</P>
                  <P>- Utilit management;</P>
                  <P>- Cleaning, waste management and pest control services;</P>
                  <P>- Grounds maintenance;</P>
                  <P>- Catering;</P>
                  <P>- Reception;</P>
                  <P>- Goods and mail receipt and distribution services.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>As per procurement documents</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>60 %</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_QUALITY>
               <AC_COST>
                  <AC_CRITERION>As per procurement documents</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>40 %</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_COST>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
